  "prompt": "What is the difference between a violin and a fiddle?",
  "response": "There is no fundamental difference between a violin and a fiddle in terms of the physical instrument. Both refer to the same four-stringed musical instrument. The main difference is in the style of music and playing technique:\n\n1. Musical style:\n- Violin is typically associated with classical music\n- Fiddle is associated with folk, country, bluegrass, and traditional music\n\n2. Playing technique:\n- Classical violin playing tends to be more formal and precise\n- Fiddle playing is often more relaxed and improvisational\n\n3. Cultural context:\n- Violin is seen as a formal, classical instrument\n- Fiddle is more casual and connected to cultural traditions\n\nThe instrument itself remains the same; the terms simply reflect different musical contexts and performance styles.",
